The Afghan situation is marked by the opposite sign - no one can be relied on and no agreements are followed.
Under these conditions, Afghan security forces used to change masters every day are poorly prepared, depending on how convenient it is for them.
Political institutions, even if formally established, will remain a potemkin village for which patriarchal tribal relations will continue to be rampant.
Balancing the interests of various ethnic groups is extremely difficult given the inaccuracies of circumstances that complicate Pakistan and Iran’s influences even more.
Even building an "actable state", which is the minimalist objective of the entire operation, does not seem too real.
Obama's strategy's time horizon is striking with voluntarism.
